For Godfrey Ho fans there is the connection that he is the production designer on this one and there were a number of "he, he, he's" in this one with the stupid English dubbing.
The story is kind of lighthearted and many fight sequences are very average but the ones with Falcon are good as are the ones with the guy with the fan who has a great roundhouse.
Best martial arts expert is the master /teacher played by Chan Chia Kai (Mars Villa) who I would like to see again in longer fights as he had a lot of technique.
The aspect ratio and framing are all wrong and mess up the film. It's obviously a vhs tape transfer.
